    {
      "note_no": "6151",
      "note": "The ma masdariyah in Arabic, in this and the subsequent clauses, is best translated in English by nouns. Thus what would literally be \"and the (wonderful) making or construction of it\" or \"the fact of its (wonderful) construction\" is, idiomatically, \"its (wonderful) structure.\" \"The (wide) spreading out\" of the earth is rendered \"its (wide) expanse,\" and so on."
